Learning things about templates in c ++;
Templates are used to make generic code program for you that works with different data type .
suppose 
void print (int value){
cout<<value<<endl;
}
void print(string value){
cout<<value<<endl;
}
int main (){
print(5);
print(hi);
}
Now in the above program I have to write program for int & then for string ,
likewise I will have to write if multiple times for multiple datatypes , but not with templates,
here is how.
#include<iostream>
#include<templates>
template<typename T>
void print(t value){
cout<<value<<endl;
}
int main (){
print(5);// it will auto-fill the datatype for you to int .
print(hi);it will auto-fill the datatype for you to char.
}
templates are evaluated at compile time , so we can make an array of unknown size using templates and then assign value later and will be evaluated 
during compile time.
example 
#include<iostream>
#include<templates>
template<int T>
class Array{
private : 
int m_Array[T];//no size mentioned , still work becasue-)
public:                                                 | 
